'''Matthew Tiberius Ryan''' (born August 10, 1951) was the [[mayor]] of [[Binghamton, New York]] from 2006 to 2013. He served two full terms in office, his eight-year tenure being ended by a term limit.<ref>[http://www.wbng.com/news/local/Mayor-elect-Rich-David-starts-adminstrative-transition--231061691.html] Mayor-elect Rich David starts administrative transition</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.albany.edu/summit/biographies.shtml |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-05-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511004636/http://www.albany.edu/summit/biographies.shtml |archivedate=2013-05-11 |df= }} Matt Ryan bio</ref> He was elected, in 2005, on the tickets of the [[New York State Democratic Committee|Democratic Party]] and the [[Working Families Party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gobroomecounty.com/files/elections/pdfs/2005OfficialGeneralElectionResults.pdf|title=Broome County Board of Elections - General election 11/08/2005|publisher=Broome County Board of Elections|accessdate=21 February 2015}}</ref> He was re-elected in 2009, defeating his eventual successor, the [[New York Republican State Committee|Republican]] candidate [[Richard C. David|Rich David]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ithacajournal.com/article/20130824/NEWS01/308240041/Rich-David-Binghamton-mayoral-candidate-goes-back-basic-|title=Rich David: Binghamton mayoral candidate goes 'back to basic'|date=24 August 2013|work=Ithaca Journal|accessdate=21 February 2015}}</ref>
