'''Oliver "Ollie" Bridge Garrett''' (October 14, 1894 – November 14, 1979) was the head of [[Boston]]'s Vice and Liquor Squad during [[Prohibition in the United States|Prohibition]].<ref>[http://www.newenglandhistoricalsociety.com/flashback-photo-oliver-garrett-bostons-booze-busting-million-dollar-cop/] </ref>  In May 1930, he pleaded guilty to charges of extortion and sentenced to two years in [[Deer Island Prison]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unionparkpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DrinkingBoston_Sample.pdf |format=PDF |title=Drinking Boston |publisher=Unionparkpress.com |accessdate=2015-02-27}}</ref>

A mixed drink, the "Million Dollar Cop", at Carrie Nation Restaurant and Cocktail Club in Boston is named after him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carrienationcocktailclub.com/drinks/ |title=Signature Cocktails &#124; Carrie Nation Restaurant Boston |publisher=Carrienationcocktailclub.com |date= |accessdate=2014-03-17}}</ref>

He was born October 14, 1894 in [[Mechanic Falls, Maine]] and died November 14, 1979 in [[Yacolt, Washington]].  He is interred at Evergreen Memorial Gardens in [[Vancouver, Washington]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~waclacem/EvergreenMemorial/e-g.pdf |format=PDF |title=G: Oliver Garrett |publisher=Rootsweb.ancestry.com |accessdate=2015-02-27}}</ref>

